What is a class in Java ?

A class in Java is a blueprint for creating the objects. It defines the properties and behavior that acts upon
these properties.

Syntax:

class ClassName {

}

Instance Variables: Variables defined inside the class are called instance variables. 
Members of class: Variables and methods defined inside the class together are called members of the class. 

A class does not take any space in the memory. 

Components of class: 

- Access modifiers
- class keyword
- class name 
- super class (if any - extends keyword)
- interface (if any - implements keyword)
- body {}
  - variables
  - constructors 
  - methods 